      <section id="idproblem11b"><title>Problem 11b – Instructions</title><para id="idprob11b">Explain why we are using the "if then else" to manipulate the input data in the example below.</para>
<example id="fs-id6221200">
<title>C++ source code</title>
<para id="fs-id25419849"><preformat id="fs-id6543855" display="block"><code>
cout &lt;&lt; "\nEnter one side of the rectangle ---------&gt;: " ;
cin &gt;&gt; side1; 
cout &lt;&lt; "\nEnter the other side of the rectangle ---&gt;: " ;
cin &gt;&gt; side2;

if (side1 &gt; side2)
  {
  length = side1;
  width = side2;
  }
else
  {
  length = side2;
  width = side1;
  } </code></preformat>
</para>
</example>
